00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:10,110
Characters, actions, occupations and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

2
00:00:10,110 --> 00:00:15,001
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

3
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:17,860
Viewer discretion is advised.

4
00:00:18,602 --> 00:00:20,960
When are you coming back?

5
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:22,611
I’ll be away for just two days. Will be back in no time.

6
00:00:22,611 --> 00:00:23,958
I promise

7
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:25,699
I will be a good boy.

8
00:00:25,782 --> 00:00:26,887
Teacher Prince is sick.

9
00:00:26,887 --> 00:00:28,120
Aou is nursing him.

10
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:31,240
Don’t let him be alone with Aou. Got it?

11
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,432
(Are you the one Kuafah met on the mountain?)

12
00:00:33,432 --> 00:00:35,631
(I’m Kitty, his girlfriend.)

13
00:00:35,631 --> 00:00:37,494
A girl called this number.

14
00:00:37,494 --> 00:00:38,774
Teacher Prince took the call.

15
00:00:38,774 --> 00:00:42,258
I will be so happy if you can climb the Himalayas again.

16
00:00:42,258 --> 00:00:45,364
If that person can inspire you to climb again,

17
00:00:45,521 --> 00:00:46,647
don’t let that person go.

18
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:48,049
I’m back.

19
00:00:48,955 --> 00:00:49,740
You.

20
00:00:53,758 --> 00:00:55,715
Don’t you have a birthday party to get to?

21
00:00:56,898 --> 00:00:57,774
Ah!

22
00:00:57,774 --> 00:01:00,311
My little brother has got something urgent to do.

23
00:01:00,625 --> 00:01:02,218
So he postponed the party.

24
00:01:02,218 --> 00:01:03,427
That’s why I hurried back.

25
00:01:04,569 --> 00:01:05,529
Right.

26
00:01:06,726 --> 00:01:07,575
Hey.

27
00:01:07,575 --> 00:01:12,357
About last night…

28
00:01:12,357 --> 00:01:14,754
Teacher Prince, we have a situation.

29
00:01:14,754 --> 00:01:16,742
Wee-ah and Sompor are fighting.

30
00:01:16,742 --> 00:01:17,590
What?

31
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:25,718
Sompor,

32
00:02:26,436 --> 00:02:28,150
do you have anything to say to Wee-ah?

33
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:31,592
I’m sorry, Wee-ah.

34
00:02:33,630 --> 00:02:34,803
Wee-ah,

35
00:02:35,234 --> 00:02:36,520
do you have anything to say?

36
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:38,880
I’m not wrong. Why should I say sorry?

37
00:02:39,388 --> 00:02:40,367
Wee-ah,

38
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,299
I heard the story from Sompor.

39
00:02:42,865 --> 00:02:45,440
She said you broke your word.

40
00:02:45,616 --> 00:02:50,480
You said you would buy her a birthday gift.

41
00:02:50,713 --> 00:02:54,459
But you bought gifts for other girls too. Is that right?

42
00:02:56,036 --> 00:02:59,184
But I don’t think Wee-ah did anything wrong.

43
00:02:59,662 --> 00:03:00,577
What?

44
00:03:00,881 --> 00:03:05,920
He promised to buy her a present.

45
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,737
And he did.

46
00:03:08,519 --> 00:03:12,098
Buying things for other people at the same time isn’t breaking the promise.

47
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,472
That’s right.

48
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,245
Why are you mad?

49
00:03:16,801 --> 00:03:17,928
Wee-ah,

50
00:03:18,801 --> 00:03:20,224
this is about feeling.

51
00:03:20,914 --> 00:03:24,541
Though you didn’t mean to, you let her down.

52
00:03:26,017 --> 00:03:27,443
Aren’t you going to say sorry?

53
00:03:33,838 --> 00:03:36,269
If you let someone down and don’t apologize,

54
00:03:39,274 --> 00:03:42,840
you will grow up to be a bad adult.

55
00:03:43,525 --> 00:03:47,120
Are you talking about me?

56
00:03:48,119 --> 00:03:48,848
No.

57
00:03:49,661 --> 00:03:50,932
I’m talking to Wee-ah here.

58
00:03:51,081 --> 00:03:54,080
You talked to him but looked at me.

59
00:03:54,821 --> 00:03:58,543
If you did nothing wrong, you have nothing to worry about.

60
00:04:00,197 --> 00:04:00,965
See?

61
00:04:01,205 --> 00:04:02,920
You were talking about me.

62
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,850
I said I was talking about the kids.

63
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:06,562
Why is it so hard for you to understand?

64
00:04:06,562 --> 00:04:10,309
Talking about the kids? Then why did you say he would grow up to be a bad adult?

65
00:04:10,674 --> 00:04:12,315
You’re referring to me.

66
00:04:12,315 --> 00:04:13,720
Calm down.

67
00:04:45,678 --> 00:04:48,120
Happy birthday, Dao.

68
00:04:52,503 --> 00:04:53,929
Thank you.

69
00:05:03,586 --> 00:05:05,873
I wish you a very good year.

70
00:05:09,325 --> 00:05:12,736
It’s already good because you’re with me.

71
00:05:17,255 --> 00:05:20,000
But let me sleep 10 more minutes, please.

72
00:05:21,736 --> 00:05:23,042
Of course.

73
00:05:39,497 --> 00:05:41,784
If the kids didn’t stop me,

74
00:05:42,039 --> 00:05:43,513
I’d definitely fight him.

75
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,001
Do you guys get me?

76
00:05:45,432 --> 00:05:46,635
I do.

77
00:05:47,043 --> 00:05:48,708
But I think you’re still at fault this time.

78
00:05:48,817 --> 00:05:50,458
You even had a guilty conscience.

79
00:05:50,673 --> 00:05:51,473
What?

80
00:05:51,973 --> 00:05:55,504
You promised him before you left you would behave.

81
00:05:55,504 --> 00:05:57,384
But you got wasted

82
00:05:57,748 --> 00:05:59,748
and that girl called and bothered him.

83
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:02,655
Do you think that a good adult should be?

84
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:06,950
It wasn’t a big deal.

85
00:06:07,618 --> 00:06:08,924
Besides,

86
00:06:10,001 --> 00:06:12,001
He and I aren’t a thing.

87
00:06:12,781 --> 00:06:14,231
You get me, don’t you, Mesa?

88
00:06:14,662 --> 00:06:15,610
I do.

89
00:06:16,966 --> 00:06:20,000
But if he’s nothing to you, why the heck did you give him the promise?

90
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:20,818
What?

91
00:06:21,721 --> 00:06:23,554
You guys are my friends.

92
00:06:23,554 --> 00:06:24,814
How about you take my side?

93
00:06:25,125 --> 00:06:25,905
No.

94
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:31,648
Someone like you will never change no matter how much time passes.

95
00:06:31,648 --> 00:06:32,626
You’re never regretful.

96
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:35,655
Make it up to him.

97
00:06:37,915 --> 00:06:39,413
How would I do that?

98
00:06:39,794 --> 00:06:44,306
All I got today was anger radiation from him

99
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,728
Like this.

100
00:06:46,601 --> 00:06:49,558
Do what you do best, manipulate.

101
00:06:49,911 --> 00:06:51,911
Pretend to get sick.

102
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,268
He will have a pity for you.

103
00:06:56,742 --> 00:06:57,938
Interesting.

104
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,345
Did you just say I’m manipulative?

105
00:07:00,345 --> 00:07:01,259
Just realized that?

106
00:07:02,586 --> 00:07:03,360
Come on.

107
00:07:03,671 --> 00:07:07,839
Tomorrow, pretend to be sick.

108
00:07:08,105 --> 00:07:10,368
I will tell the children you’re sick.

109
00:07:10,483 --> 00:07:12,483
And they will spread the news.

110
00:07:12,622 --> 00:07:14,622
It’s more reliable that way.

111
00:07:14,622 --> 00:07:15,937
He will believe you’re really sick.

112
00:07:21,645 --> 00:07:24,219
Gosh! Dr. Fah has a serious stomach ache?

113
00:07:24,219 --> 00:07:25,489
Keep it between us.

114
00:07:25,489 --> 00:07:26,952
Don’t make people panic.

115
00:07:26,952 --> 00:07:28,369
Trust me on that.

116
00:07:29,110 --> 00:07:30,703
Hot news!

117
00:07:30,862 --> 00:07:33,520
What? Dr. Fah is pregnant?

118
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,388
What?

119
00:07:39,299 --> 00:07:40,916
Teacher Prince.

120
00:07:41,847 --> 00:07:46,160
Is it true that Dr. Fah is sick and you are pregnant?

121
00:07:46,707 --> 00:07:48,707
Sompor.

122
00:07:50,549 --> 00:07:54,463
I think there’re some misunderstandings here.

123
00:07:59,784 --> 00:08:00,665
Doctor.

124
00:08:01,287 --> 00:08:02,191
Hey.

125
00:08:03,565 --> 00:08:06,737
Did you spread a weird rumor to the kids?

126
00:08:07,231 --> 00:08:08,106
Hey!

127
00:08:09,231 --> 00:08:10,212
JJ.

128
00:08:11,359 --> 00:08:12,761
Why are you here?

129
00:08:13,281 --> 00:08:14,322
Teacher Prince.

130
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:17,783
I’m in charge here for Kuafah.

131
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,416
And…

132
00:08:20,775 --> 00:08:22,031
where is he?

133
00:08:23,008 --> 00:08:24,601
He has a stomach ache.

134
00:08:24,601 --> 00:08:25,767
He’s resting at his house alone.

135
00:08:26,478 --> 00:08:27,856
Poor him.

136
00:08:28,565 --> 00:08:30,565
He’s a doctor.

137
00:08:30,722 --> 00:08:33,631
But when a doctor gets sick, no one takes care of him.

138
00:08:44,256 --> 00:08:45,474
It’s me.

139
00:08:45,474 --> 00:08:46,472
Are you in?

140
00:08:47,344 --> 00:08:48,866
Ouch!

141
00:08:48,866 --> 00:08:50,328
I am.

142
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,863
I brought you congee and antacid.

143
00:09:02,852 --> 00:09:04,637
I heard you have acid reflux.

144
00:09:05,881 --> 00:09:07,060
Thank you.

145
00:09:07,204 --> 00:09:08,432
Argh!

146
00:09:09,126 --> 00:09:09,980
Ouch!

147
00:09:10,195 --> 00:09:11,045
Are you okay?

148
00:09:11,294 --> 00:09:12,097
I am.

149
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,358
Oh!

150
00:09:16,358 --> 00:09:21,210
Ouch!

151
00:09:21,766 --> 00:09:23,288
You don’t look okay at all.

152
00:09:24,014 --> 00:09:24,730
Here.

153
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:25,799
Let me help.

154
00:09:58,475 --> 00:09:59,608
Is it all right?

155
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:01,342
Of course.

156
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:02,299
It’s good.

157
00:10:56,674 --> 00:10:59,726
Take the medicine and get some rest.

158
00:11:00,288 --> 00:11:01,504
I’ll just leave now.

159
00:11:01,815 --> 00:11:02,599
Hold on.

160
00:11:05,444 --> 00:11:06,937
I’ve got something to say to you.

161
00:11:11,266 --> 00:11:12,204
What is it?

162
00:11:13,765 --> 00:11:14,554
I…

163
00:11:16,109 --> 00:11:17,966
I want to explain about the other night.

164
00:11:20,236 --> 00:11:21,506
You don’t have to.

165
00:11:21,506 --> 00:11:22,440
Just get some rest.

166
00:11:22,736 --> 00:11:23,787
I can’t.

167
00:11:24,002 --> 00:11:27,319
If I don’t get this out, I won’t be able to sleep.

168
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:32,153
That night, I didn’t mean to go out and get drunk.

169
00:11:32,549 --> 00:11:37,635
My brother’s boyfriend took me there.

170
00:11:39,317 --> 00:11:41,054
And how old are you now?

171
00:11:41,196 --> 00:11:42,360
Don’t you know how to say no?

172
00:11:42,787 --> 00:11:45,194
I went out just to drink.

173
00:11:45,194 --> 00:11:47,867
I just didn’t think I’d be that drunk.

174
00:11:48,161 --> 00:11:53,653
And the girl who called you took my phone when I was using the restroom.

175
00:11:54,277 --> 00:11:55,769
What she said was all nonsense.

176
00:11:56,032 --> 00:11:57,066
She isn’t my girlfriend.

177
00:12:00,001 --> 00:12:03,920
What she is to you doesn’t concern me.

178
00:12:04,186 --> 00:12:05,171
It does.

179
00:12:06,186 --> 00:12:07,655
You’re mad at me.

180
00:12:09,087 --> 00:12:10,166
I’m not.

181
00:12:10,668 --> 00:12:11,900
You are.

182
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:14,513
I can tell from your voice you’re mad.

183
00:12:14,513 --> 00:12:19,625
If I didn’t pretend I was sick to get you here,
I wouldn’t know you’re this mad.

184
00:12:19,769 --> 00:12:20,650
Oops!

185
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:25,410
It’s not that.

186
00:12:25,410 --> 00:12:26,039
I mean…

187
00:12:26,039 --> 00:12:27,769
Do you think I’m that silly?

188
00:12:27,769 --> 00:12:29,793
I didn’t mean it that way.

189
00:12:29,793 --> 00:12:32,822
I just don’t want you to be jealous over nothing.

190
00:12:34,434 --> 00:12:35,420
Damn!

191
00:12:35,779 --> 00:12:38,348
You’re a jerk and a narcissist.

192
00:12:39,857 --> 00:12:40,842
What a waste of time.

193
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,264
Hey.

194
00:12:43,368 --> 00:12:44,292
Hey.

195
00:12:46,558 --> 00:12:48,175
I heard there was a fight.

196
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:49,809
Pretty bad.

197
00:12:50,001 --> 00:12:52,766
You should help him with the sports day thing.

198
00:12:52,766 --> 00:12:53,959
That way you can be close to him.

199
00:12:53,959 --> 00:12:56,985
Let’s make it fun then.

200
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,704
I will help you with that.

201
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:00,389
Thank you.

202
00:13:34,793 --> 00:13:35,556
Hey.

203
00:13:35,713 --> 00:13:36,726
Mesa.

204
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,269
Did you forget something?

205
00:13:39,357 --> 00:13:40,198
No.

206
00:13:40,740 --> 00:13:42,043
I came to talk to you.

207
00:13:42,876 --> 00:13:45,616
I heard there was a fight.

208
00:13:47,355 --> 00:13:48,143
Yes.

209
00:13:48,592 --> 00:13:49,804
Pretty bad.

210
00:13:51,697 --> 00:13:54,482
That’s what I heard.

211
00:13:55,164 --> 00:13:57,164
If you want my help, feel free to ask.

212
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,155
Are you sure?

213
00:14:01,806 --> 00:14:02,622
Of course.

214
00:14:02,986 --> 00:14:04,784
I know both parties.

215
00:14:04,989 --> 00:14:07,258
I don’t want the fight to keep going.

216
00:14:08,856 --> 00:14:11,936
I’d like to ask you one thing then.

217
00:14:19,546 --> 00:14:24,296
Can you hand this to the village chief for me?

218
00:14:24,296 --> 00:14:27,620
You wrote a letter to my friend…

219
00:14:28,456 --> 00:14:29,122
Wait.

220
00:14:29,459 --> 00:14:30,236
The village chief?

221
00:14:31,358 --> 00:14:32,207
Yes.

222
00:14:32,591 --> 00:14:36,094
This is a permission letter to organize a sports day in the village.

223
00:14:37,492 --> 00:14:38,289
A sports day?

224
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:41,781
Because of the fight between Wee-ah and Sompor.

225
00:14:42,301 --> 00:14:46,936
This idea is to amend their relationship.

226
00:14:47,847 --> 00:14:52,225
So the fight you mentioned…

227
00:14:52,324 --> 00:14:53,645
It’s Wee-ah and Sompor.

228
00:14:54,228 --> 00:14:56,051
Wee-ah and Sompor.

229
00:14:56,749 --> 00:14:57,475
Yes.

230
00:14:59,113 --> 00:15:00,926
So this is for the village chief.

231
00:15:01,288 --> 00:15:02,019
Yes.

232
00:15:03,051 --> 00:15:03,871
Got it.

233
00:15:10,084 --> 00:15:13,789
So he’s only concerned with the kids fighting.

234
00:15:13,789 --> 00:15:15,324
He doesn’t even care about you at all.

235
00:15:16,605 --> 00:15:17,800
Hell yes.

236
00:15:18,095 --> 00:15:19,259
I’m so pissed.

237
00:15:19,845 --> 00:15:22,630
How do I patch things up with him?

238
00:15:22,874 --> 00:15:24,313
I already faked my sickness.

239
00:15:24,313 --> 00:15:27,337
How about you fake your death this time?

240
00:15:27,456 --> 00:15:28,676
Maybe he’ll forgive you.

241
00:15:28,676 --> 00:15:31,879
What a smart idea.

242
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,555
Fah!

243
00:15:37,328 --> 00:15:39,128
How on earth did you come up with that?

244
00:15:39,128 --> 00:15:40,383
One more scoop, please.

245
00:15:41,456 --> 00:15:45,835
I think you should help him with the sports day thing.

246
00:15:46,141 --> 00:15:47,670
That way you can be close to him.

247
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:48,657
That’s right.

248
00:15:48,657 --> 00:15:49,586
Good idea.

249
00:15:49,684 --> 00:15:52,604
Show him your hard work. He might come around.

250
00:15:53,553 --> 00:15:54,252
Fine.

251
00:15:55,688 --> 00:15:57,169
I will try.

252
00:15:58,278 --> 00:15:59,501
Thank you guys so much.

253
00:15:59,501 --> 00:16:00,278
Here is your reward.

254
00:16:00,278 --> 00:16:02,159
Argh!

255
00:16:04,357 --> 00:16:07,928
The kids should be so proud to have such a caring teacher.

256
00:16:09,471 --> 00:16:10,311
No.

257
00:16:10,603 --> 00:16:12,863
You’re the one who cares about them.

258
00:16:13,731 --> 00:16:15,191
You’ve brought them lots of snacks.

259
00:16:15,617 --> 00:16:17,099
They should be so happy.

260
00:16:17,764 --> 00:16:18,905
I’m happy too

261
00:16:19,416 --> 00:16:20,567
to see you smile.

262
00:16:22,371 --> 00:16:25,416
I mean I’m happy to see the kids smile.

263
00:16:36,415 --> 00:16:37,286
Excuse me.

264
00:16:37,645 --> 00:16:38,729
You’ve got the paint there.

265
00:16:48,044 --> 00:16:48,956
Okay.

266
00:16:52,703 --> 00:16:54,711
Hey, Dr. Fah.

267
00:16:56,195 --> 00:16:57,692
Are you here to help?

268
00:16:59,196 --> 00:17:00,170
Yes.

269
00:17:00,976 --> 00:17:04,524
But I see there’s nothing for me to do.

270
00:17:05,056 --> 00:17:06,211
I’m not needed.

271
00:17:06,211 --> 00:17:07,752
You are.

272
00:17:07,952 --> 00:17:09,305
There’s a lot left to do.

273
00:17:09,485 --> 00:17:10,312
Please.

274
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:16,898
Here.

275
00:17:17,481 --> 00:17:18,189
Yes.

276
00:17:19,109 --> 00:17:21,813
Where should I paint?

277
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:23,146
That’s not for painting.

278
00:17:23,326 --> 00:17:24,866
Please clean it for me.

279
00:17:24,866 --> 00:17:26,242
I will change the colors.

280
00:17:28,813 --> 00:17:30,274
Let’s not bother him.

281
