00:35:25,953 --> 00:35:27,953
Teacher Prince, are you okay?

565
00:35:28,292 --> 00:35:29,675
I am.

566
00:35:30,095 --> 00:35:31,202
Just warming up.

567
00:35:31,485 --> 00:35:35,418
We will be competing in three sports.

568
00:35:35,418 --> 00:35:38,596
The team that gets to the finish line first wins.

569
00:35:39,003 --> 00:35:45,553
If you’re ready, 3 2 1, go!

570
00:35:46,302 --> 00:35:49,795
The game has started.

571
00:35:49,795 --> 00:35:52,194
They are eating as fast as they can.

572
00:35:52,194 --> 00:35:54,981
Go. Go. Go. Do your best, everyone!

573
00:36:00,089 --> 00:36:02,626
The blue team is in the lead.

574
00:36:02,747 --> 00:36:06,987
The white team is tailing them so closely. So so so close.

575
00:36:17,485 --> 00:36:18,552
Come on.

576
00:36:18,552 --> 00:36:19,938
Faster.

577
00:36:22,898 --> 00:36:24,178
Tag my hand.

578
00:36:24,178 --> 00:36:25,201
Let’s go.

579
00:36:25,666 --> 00:36:28,203
We’ve just started the second competition.

580
00:36:28,203 --> 00:36:30,444
What a close game.

581
00:36:30,750 --> 00:36:32,423
No way.

582
00:36:32,423 --> 00:36:34,447
The blue team is so much ahead.

583
00:36:34,447 --> 00:36:36,479
Can the white team catch up?

584
00:36:36,479 --> 00:36:39,359
Keep going. Keep cycling, my friend.

585
00:36:45,043 --> 00:36:46,061
It’s your turn now, Teacher Prince.

586
00:36:46,061 --> 00:36:49,858
- We’ve come to a three-legged race now.
- Let’s go, Sompor.

587
00:36:51,665 --> 00:36:53,665
The blue team has just started.

588
00:36:53,665 --> 00:36:56,618
I wonder if they can level it up at all.

589
00:36:56,618 --> 00:36:59,028
Teacher Prince has gone so far now.

590
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,178
Teacher Prince, are you all right?

591
00:37:05,145 --> 00:37:07,145
Fah, come on.

592
00:37:08,102 --> 00:37:14,675
- Blue!
- White!

593
00:37:18,020 --> 00:37:21,018
Oops! What is going on over there?

594
00:37:21,095 --> 00:37:22,745
Teacher Prince just fell all of a sudden.

595
00:37:22,745 --> 00:37:25,019
Fah, it’s your chance now. Surpass him.

596
00:37:26,244 --> 00:37:27,818
Dr. Fah, why are you stopping?

597
00:37:28,332 --> 00:37:32,479
The blue team, keep going!

598
00:37:32,653 --> 00:37:33,978
Let’s help Teacher Prince up.

599
00:37:49,063 --> 00:37:49,759
Come on.

600
00:37:50,039 --> 00:37:51,343
Let’s go to the finish line together.

601
00:37:56,422 --> 00:38:01,245
Wow! Dr. Fah comes back and helps Teacher Prince up.

602
00:38:01,245 --> 00:38:05,604
What a lovely ship. No! I mean what an impressive race.

603
00:38:13,858 --> 00:38:16,348
And they finally get to the finish line together.

604
00:38:21,317 --> 00:38:26,304
The blue and white teams finished at the same time as a result of today's competition.

605
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:28,376
We have a tie game.

606
00:38:30,348 --> 00:38:38,204
No matter who wins or loses, every contestant will get a medal.

607
00:38:45,958 --> 00:38:48,168
Teacher Prince, is this the real gold?

608
00:38:49,396 --> 00:38:50,828
It’s a chocolate medal.

609
00:38:50,991 --> 00:38:52,018
So delicious.

610
00:38:53,575 --> 00:38:55,365
That’s only a consolation prize.

611
00:38:56,457 --> 00:39:01,231
What you best deserve is this one.

612
00:39:02,641 --> 00:39:03,622
Hey.

613
00:39:05,092 --> 00:39:06,298
How did you get it?

614
00:39:07,115 --> 00:39:09,656
Before the competition started,

615
00:39:10,286 --> 00:39:11,681
I went looking for it.

616
00:39:12,736 --> 00:39:13,934
Besides,

617
00:39:14,643 --> 00:39:16,045
I know everything, Wee-ah.

618
00:39:16,222 --> 00:39:17,224
Know what?

619
00:39:17,457 --> 00:39:24,101
You gave plain hair clips to other girls.

620
00:39:24,412 --> 00:39:28,092
But the one you gave Sompor was custom-made.

621
00:39:29,038 --> 00:39:30,041
That’s right.

622
00:39:31,861 --> 00:39:35,308
I chose a pink hair clip because Sompor likes pink.

623
00:39:36,362 --> 00:39:40,719
Why didn’t you tell Sompor from the beginning?

624
00:39:40,859 --> 00:39:42,156
Because it’s not cool.

625
00:39:44,956 --> 00:39:50,139
But I think it’s much cooler telling the truth.

626
00:39:50,602 --> 00:39:53,675
It’s not too late to tell her.

627
00:39:54,464 --> 00:39:57,841
The sooner you tell, the sooner you’ll look cool.

628
00:40:00,227 --> 00:40:00,960
Come on.

629
00:40:01,450 --> 00:40:02,344
Yes, sir.

630
00:40:12,032 --> 00:40:14,965
How is your ankle?

631
00:40:18,074 --> 00:40:19,036
It’s all right.

632
00:40:19,853 --> 00:40:20,891
Thank you.

633
00:40:21,349 --> 00:40:24,702
Let’s get you bandaged.

634
00:40:24,959 --> 00:40:25,711
Come on.

635
00:40:34,141 --> 00:40:37,261
HEALTH CENTER

636
00:40:41,433 --> 00:40:43,433
You got a sprained ankle. You should be fine.

637
00:40:45,162 --> 00:40:47,582
Next time, don’t force it.

638
00:40:48,088 --> 00:40:52,468
That’s why you looked painful when you ran.

639
00:40:53,359 --> 00:40:54,459
Thank you.

640
00:40:56,979 --> 00:40:58,206
Your welcome.

641
00:40:58,548 --> 00:41:01,271
It’s a duty of a doctor to take care of his patients.

642
00:41:03,899 --> 00:41:08,046
I mean thank you for taking me to the finish line with you.

643
00:41:08,899 --> 00:41:11,109
And for finding the hair clip for Wee-ah.

644
00:41:24,616 --> 00:41:25,581
- I’m sorry.
- I’m sorry.

645
00:41:28,898 --> 00:41:30,190
You first.

646
00:41:33,314 --> 00:41:35,314
I’m sorry for being unreasonable.

647
00:41:36,814 --> 00:41:39,561
There’s no reason for me to be angry at you about that night.

648
00:41:43,544 --> 00:41:46,337
What if I say I get you?

649
00:41:48,089 --> 00:41:50,463
What do you mean?

650
00:41:50,949 --> 00:41:54,513
Yayah told me what you’ve been through.

651
00:41:55,651 --> 00:41:57,184
What do you mean, Yayah?

652
00:41:58,384 --> 00:42:03,418
Teacher Prince told me he had a terrible ex.

653
00:42:05,027 --> 00:42:08,418
That person couldn’t provide him with clarity.

654
00:42:08,731 --> 00:42:10,451
He came when he wanted to.

655
00:42:10,451 --> 00:42:12,089
He went with someone else when he felt like it.

656
00:42:12,329 --> 00:42:13,769
Teacher Prince couldn’t even get jealous.

657
00:42:14,011 --> 00:42:15,801
Because there was no established relationship.

658
00:42:16,870 --> 00:42:19,477
What did Teacher Prince do?

659
00:42:20,281 --> 00:42:22,064
They were together for a brief amount of time.

660
00:42:22,064 --> 00:42:24,498
Teacher Prince couldn’t endure it at last.

661
00:42:24,498 --> 00:42:25,499
He broke up with that person.

662
00:42:26,124 --> 00:42:30,691
And what you’re doing is a repeat of what his ex did to him.

663
00:42:31,389 --> 00:42:33,298
No wonder why he’s mad.

664
00:42:34,061 --> 00:42:36,504
He doesn’t want to get hurt again.

665
00:42:40,758 --> 00:42:45,394
Just because I’m not being clear doesn’t mean I’m not serious with you.

666
00:42:46,751 --> 00:42:53,114
But I’m so serious that I’m afraid it’s too soon.

667
00:42:54,497 --> 00:42:57,500
I’d been with my ex for seven years yet we couldn’t make it.

668
00:42:58,565 --> 00:43:01,288
That’s why I don’t want to rush things.

669
00:43:03,898 --> 00:43:05,898
But if my actions get you the wrong idea,

670
00:43:20,514 --> 00:43:22,281
from this moment on,

671
00:43:25,801 --> 00:43:27,241
can I flirt on you?

672
00:43:38,416 --> 00:43:39,295
Prince,

673
00:43:39,618 --> 00:43:41,369
I’m returning the cap gun I borrowed.

674
00:43:43,076 --> 00:43:43,734
Oops!

675
00:43:44,387 --> 00:43:45,938
Am I interrupting?

676
00:43:46,540 --> 00:43:47,458
No.

677
00:43:48,495 --> 00:43:50,487
Will you please excuse me?

678
00:43:57,576 --> 00:43:58,549
Thank you.

679
00:44:07,901 --> 00:44:08,931
What were you two talking about?

680
00:44:11,544 --> 00:44:12,981
What was it?

681
00:44:13,785 --> 00:44:14,852
Nothing.

682
00:44:15,249 --> 00:44:17,092
I was just giving him first aid.

683
00:44:35,247 --> 00:44:36,453
Where are you going?

684
00:44:40,210 --> 00:44:43,738
That gunshot was a signal to start.

685
00:44:44,094 --> 00:44:47,284
This game isn’t going to be as easy as the one we competed in today.

686
00:44:48,489 --> 00:44:49,952
We’ll see about that.

687
00:44:50,555 --> 00:44:54,188
Because I never lose.

688
00:45:13,131 --> 00:45:15,738
I just want to try hard.

689
00:45:16,134 --> 00:45:18,898
I want to stop everything…just to be with him.

690
00:45:21,179 --> 00:45:23,786
Directed by Siwaj Sawatmaneekul

691
00:45:46,153 --> 00:45:46,955
Hey!

692
00:45:46,955 --> 00:45:47,978
What are you doing?

693
00:45:47,979 --> 00:45:49,979
You allowed me to flirt on you.

694
00:45:49,979 --> 00:45:53,435
From now on, I’ll just flirt on you non-stop.

695
00:45:53,435 --> 00:45:54,824
Prepare yourself for that.

696
00:45:55,658 --> 00:45:58,708
Can I put my hand right here until it gets warmer?

697
00:45:59,034 --> 00:46:00,427
Prince, this way.

698
00:46:00,576 --> 00:46:02,763
Teacher Prince already has someone he’s talking to.

699
00:46:02,983 --> 00:46:04,260
Don’t worry.

700
00:46:04,260 --> 00:46:05,696
I’m not trying to steal him.

701
00:46:05,767 --> 00:46:09,470
I just want him to meet someone who can take care of him better than me.

702
00:46:09,579 --> 00:46:10,635
What are you doing?

703
00:46:10,635 --> 00:46:15,242
Your friend should know you have a doctor to take care of you up on the mountain.

